cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and semantic parsing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents an end-to-end model for cross-lingual semantic parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses a novel copy mechanism in the model. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the model is based on neural networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents an evaluation metric to measure the similarity between system output and reference meaning representations.
